## Front page
frontpage.title                                                 = Start page
frontpage.heading                                               = Sign up to report your income and expenses quarterly
frontpage.line_1                                                = Thank you for agreeing to take part in this HM Revenue and Customs pilot.
frontpage.line_2                                                = By signing up you’re helping us to test a new way of working out your tax. You’ll do this by:
frontpage.bullet_1                                              = using your accounting software to record your income and expenses
frontpage.bullet_2                                              = sending details to us regularly from May 2017
frontpage.line_3                                                = Soon this will replace your annual tax return but you’ll still need to send us your 2016 to 2017 tax return and pay any tax you owe by 31 January 2018.
frontpage.line_4                                                = Your information will be secure. You’ll need to go through security checks first to make sure no one else can access your personal details.
frontpage.line_5                                                = If at any time during the pilot you decide not to take part you can stop but you may need to start using this way of working out your tax from April 2018.
frontpage.line_6                                                = You can sign up if:
frontpage.bullet_3                                              = you’re a sole trader
frontpage.bullet_4                                              = you rent out a UK property
frontpage.bullet_5                                              = you’re a sole trader and rent out a UK property
frontpage.bullet_6                                              = you’re willing to go paperless
frontpage.bullet_7                                              = your current accounting period starts on or after 1 April 2017
frontpage.line_7                                                = Use the user ID and password you got when you signed up to the Self Assessment online service.
frontpage.second.heading                                        = What happens next
frontpage.line_8                                                = You’ll need to:
frontpage.bullet_8                                              = keep using accounting software to keep your records and send regular reports
frontpage.bullet_9                                              = send your summary report for the tax year 2017 to 2018 by 31 January 2019 at the latest
frontpage.line_9                                                = You’ll get:
frontpage.bullet_10                                             = a reference number to you may need if you contact us
frontpage.bullet_11                                             = an estimate of what you owe every time you send a report
frontpage.line_10                                               = You can
frontpage.bullet_12                                             = use your business tax account to look at your reports from June 2017
frontpage.bullet_13                                             = choose to pay as you go

